 :snark: /n./ [Lewis Carroll, via the Michigan Terminal System] 1. A system
failure. When a user's process bombed, the operator would get the message
"Help, Help, Snark in MTS!" 2. More generally, any kind of unexplained or
threatening event on a computer (especially if it might be a boojum). Often
used to refer to an event or a log file entry that might indicate an
attempted security violation. see {snivitz}. 3. UUCP name of
snark.thyrsus.com, home site of the Jargon File versions from 2.*.* on (i.e.,
this lexicon).